==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inosculation
<hw>In*os`cu*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>inosculation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The junction or connection of
vessels, channels, or passages, so that their contents pass from one to
the other; union by mouths or ducts; anastomosis; intercommunication;
<as>as, <ex>inosculation</ex> of veins, etc.</as></def>
<rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inosinic</ent>⟦br⟧
